.tactic = types:forbid-as-cast

.what = forbid `as x` casts; signals rule.require.shapefit violation

.scope: all typescript code; enforced at code review and lint rules

.why: bypasses type system; hides errors; creates runtime risks; complicates refactors

.exception: allowed only at external org code boundaries; must document via inline comment; include note on removal path

.how: when tempted, ask why type doesn't fit; fix root cause; create proper types; use type guards

.enforcement: `as` casts in prod code without docs = blocker; docs must explain: why types lack, correct type, removal changes

.examples:
  .positive:
    ```ts
    // refactored to avoid cast
    const result = processinput(input); // types align

    // use type guard
    if (isvalidresponse(response)) {
      // response narrowed
    }

    // documented exception
    // note: third-party-sdk lacks types
    // todo: contribute types
    const data = response.data as thirdpartyresponse;
    ```
  .negative:
    ```ts
    // ðŸ‘Ž undocumented cast
    const user = data as user;
    ```

